{"ts": "2026-06-08T03:59:59.017514+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 0c57de2aad9ee533046b71c08b56943be304d867)", "id": "lc_12440f3c-cfc6-40ec-a830-a683e27c0d44"}, {"type": "text", "text": "const { run } = require('runjs')\nconst chalk = require('chalk')\nconst config = require('../vue.config.js')\nconst rawArgv = process.argv.slice(2)\nconst args = rawArgv.join(' ')\n\nif (process.env.npm_config_preview || rawArgv.includes('--preview')) {\n  const report = rawArgv.includes('--report')\n\n  run(`vue-cli-service build ${args}`)\n\n  const port = 9526\n  const publicPath = config.publicPath\n\n  var connect = require('connect')\n  var serveStatic = require('serve-static')\n  const app = connect()\n\n  app.use(\n    publicPath,\n    serveStatic('./dist', {\n      index: ['index.html', '/']\n    })\n  )\n\n  app.listen(port, function () {\n    console.log(chalk.green(`> Preview at  http://localhost:${port}${publicPath}`))\n    if (report) {\n      console.log(chalk.green(`> Report at  http://localhost:${port}${publicPath}report.html`))\n    }\n\n  })\n} else {\n  run(`vue-cli-service build ${args}`)\n}\n", "id": "lc_63af06ce-fffb-4794-bd78-54f0b07fa2f6"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "091109b2-225a-4924-bbaa-f88cc2f802de", "tool_call_id": "call_00_J94FE5nZlangAuYAWB553832", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:00:15.813620+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "I now have all the information needed. Here is a comprehensive summary:\n\n---\n\n## How to Start the Admin App Locally (Development)\n\n1. **Install pnpm** (if not already installed):\n   ```bash\n   npm i -g pnpm\n   ```\n\n2. **Install dependencies**:\n   ```bash\n   pnpm install\n   ```\n\n3. **Start the dev server**:\n   ```bash\n   pnpm dev\n   ```\n   This runs `vue-cli-service serve` and starts a hot-reloading dev server at **http://localhost:9528**.\n\n   The dev server also includes a **mock API server** (configured in `vue.config.js` → `devServer.before` using `mock/mock-server.js`).\n\n   Environment variables are loaded from **`.env.development`**:\n   - `ENV = 'development'`\n   - `VUE_APP_BASE_API = '/dev-api'`\n\n   The port can be overridden via:\n   ```bash\n   pnpm dev --port=3000\n   # or\n   port=3000 pnpm dev\n   ```\n\n---\n\n## How to Build / Preview for Staging\n\n### Build for staging\n```bash\npnpm build:stage\n```\nThis runs `vue-cli-service build --mode staging`, using **`.env.staging`**:\n- `NODE_ENV = production`\n- `ENV = 'staging'`\n- `VUE_APP_BASE_API = '/stage-api'`\n\nThe output is written to the **`dist/`** folder. The public path is set to `/vue3-admin-template/` (as configured in `vue.config.js`).\n\n### Preview staging build\nThere is no separate preview command for staging; the `pnpm preview` command (see below) builds the default production mode. To preview a staging build, you can build it and then serve the `dist/` folder with any static server, e.g.:\n```bash\npnpm build:stage\nnpx serve dist\n```\n\n---\n\n## How to Build / Preview for Production\n\n### Build for production\n```bash\npnpm build:prod\n```\nThis runs `vue-cli-service build` (the default mode), using **`.env.production`**:\n- `ENV = 'production'`\n- `VUE_APP_BASE_API = '/prod-api'`\n\nOutput goes to the **`dist/`** folder, with public path `/vue3-admin-template/`.\n\n### Preview the production build\n```bash\npnpm preview\n```\nThis runs `node build/index.js --preview`, which:\n1. Builds the project for production (same as `pnpm build:prod`).\n2. Serves the `dist/` directory using a lightweight Node.js `connect` server on **port 9526**.\n3. The preview URL is: **http://localhost:9526/vue3-admin-template**\n\nTo also generate a webpack bundle analysis report:\n```bash\npnpm preview -- --report\n```\nThe report is then available at `http://localhost:9526/vue3-admin-template/report.html`.\n\n---\n\n### Quick Reference Table\n\n| Environment | Command | Env File | API Base |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Dev (local)** | `pnpm dev` | `.env.development` | `/dev-api` |\n| **Build staging** | `pnpm build:stage` | `.env.staging` | `/stage-api` |\n| **Build production** | `pnpm build:prod` | `.env.production` | `/prod-api` |\n| **Preview production** | `pnpm preview` | `.env.production` | `/prod-api` |", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1160, "prompt_tokens": 10952, "total_tokens": 12112, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 383, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 10624}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 10624, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 328}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "130d3f0f-0c05-41ca-af55-83457acd9e75", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea563-262a-70f2-9354-acd7ca6dce6b-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 10952, "output_tokens": 1160, "total_tokens": 12112, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 10624}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 383}}}}]}}}
